title: Essence-25 years celebrating Black women (Art Magazine).pdf
description:
H.N. Abrams / 1995 / pdf / English / 175 pag / ISBN10 0810932563 / 22.1 MB

In 1970, Essence magazine was founded for African-American women to address a range of lifestyle issues - family, careers, personal relationships, health, education, politics and pride. This book surveys 25 years of change as reflected in the magazine, featuring photographs of famous Black women
